					<description><![CDATA[<p>IMU Biosciences has secured a $53 million (£40 million) Series A fundraising round, bringing the total raised in the round to more than double the original amount. This huge vote</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/imu-biosciences-secures-53m-to-advance-immune-tech/" data-wpel-link="internal">IMU Biosciences Secures $53M to Advance Immune Tech</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://imubiosciences.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">IMU Biosciences</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> has secured a $53 million (£40 million) Series A </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/contraline-raises-92-5m/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">fundraising </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">round, bringing the total raised in the round to more than double the original amount. This huge vote of confidence highlights the faith the market has in IMU&#8217;s AI-native strategy of the human immune system.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new round was led by IQ Capital and Molten Ventures and included strong support from British Business Bank, Meltwind and other existing institutional investors. With this new injection of capital, IMU has now raised around $60m overall, making it the world&#8217;s leading high-resolution immune profiling platform.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">From Academic Research to HD Immunology</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founded on nearly a decade of pioneering research at the Francis Crick Institute and King’s College London, IMU Biosciences aims to solve a fundamental problem in modern medicine: while the immune system is the gatekeeper of all human health, it remains notoriously difficult to measure with precision.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Standard clinical tests often provide only fragmented, low-resolution snapshots of immune activity. In contrast, IMU’s platform, which they describe as &#8220;HD Immunology&#8221;, delivers unprecedented depth. Utilising a mere 2 ml blood sample, the company’s technology can generate more than 100 million data points, classifying approximately 2,500 discrete immune cell subsets in real-time.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_202253" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202253" class="wp-image-202253 size-large" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/scientist-using-pipette-1024x642.jpg" alt="scientist using pipette" width="1024" height="642" /><p id="caption-attachment-202253" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p>Dr. John Baker, CEO of IMU Biosciences, said the immune system remains poorly understood due to fragmented and mechanistic tools. With the largest global immune system dataset, IMU is uniquely positioned to fuel discoveries, devise treatments, and empower clinicians.</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/contraline-raises-92-5m/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Contraline Raises $92.5 Million Series B to Advance NES/T Male Contraceptive Development</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Strategic Clinical Focus: Transplants and Oncology</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The $53 million infusion will be used to weaponise the company across the transition point from data discovery to a product-based approach. IMU is entering three key clinical programmes where immune status is a key part of potential success:</span></p>
<ol>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Stem Cell Transplantation:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Developing predictive tools to assess graft efficacy and improve patient matching.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Solid Organ Transplantation:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Developing methods for monitoring and predicting graft rejection prior to clinical presentation.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Immuno-Oncology:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Identifying immune signatures that can accurately predict who is likely to respond to checkpoint inhibitors and who is likely to experience significant adverse events.</span></li>
</ol>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Furthermore, this funding also helps IMU play a part in MANIFEST, a large UK-wide research project looking into the disparities in patient reactions to cancer immunotherapy. IMU aims to distinguish clearer indicators for response and relapse from studying 3,000 cancer tissue samples.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Future of Precision Medicine</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Investors see IMU as a bridge between the vast potential of the immune system and the practical needs of the clinic. Dr. Inga Deakin, Partner at Molten Ventures, noted that the platform’s ability to interrogate the immune system at this resolution has the potential to &#8220;redefine how we match the right treatment to the right patient at the right time.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As the biotech industry moves toward increasingly personalised therapies, IMU’s ability to provide a standardised, scalable, and highly detailed digital picture of immune health could prove to be the missing link in making precision medicine a reality for millions.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/imu-biosciences-secures-53m-to-advance-immune-tech/" data-wpel-link="internal">IMU Biosciences Secures $53M to Advance Immune Tech</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
