		<link>https://ventureburn.com/mecka-ai-raises-60m-to-train-robots-with-human-data/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Tue, 02 Jun 2026 14:23:33 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=202209</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>New York City-based startup Mecka AI announced the completion of $60 million in cumulative funding. The financing structure shows the rapid growth of the enterprise. It comprises a $25 million</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/mecka-ai-raises-60m-to-train-robots-with-human-data/" data-wpel-link="internal">Mecka AI Raises $60M to Train Robots With Human Data</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">New York City-based startup </span><a href="https://www.mecka.ai/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Mecka AI </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">announced the completion of $60 million in cumulative </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/blackstone-raises-13-1b-in-major-fund-boost/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. The financing structure shows the rapid growth of the enterprise. It comprises a $25 million Series A round that quietly closed in November 2025, alongside $35 million in newly secured follow-on investments. The combined capital injection was led by Framework Ventures, with strong backing from Menlo Ventures, Kindred Ventures, SV Angel, and prominent robotics researcher Ted Xiao, a former Google DeepMind specialist.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Moving Past the Limits of Simulation</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Historically, robotics companies have relied on two primary methods to teach machines physical tasks. The first is teleoperation, where a human wears a VR headset and manually guides a single robot through a motion hundreds of times. The second is digital simulation, where artificial agents practice tasks inside virtual environments.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Both paths present severe limitations. Teleoperation is notoriously slow and difficult to scale, while simulations often fail to replicate the complex physics, friction, and sensory chaos of a real human environment.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_202213" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202213" class="size-large wp-image-202213" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/circuit-board-with-brain-on-it-1024x576.jpg" alt="circuit board with brain on it" width="1024" height="576" /><p id="caption-attachment-202213" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Mecka AI is taking a fundamentally different approach by building the data and deployment layer for embodied AI out of direct, real-world human movement. Instead of relying entirely on robotic laboratories, the startup harvests first-person activity data directly from humans going about their daily lives across different environments worldwide, including residential homes, industrial kitchens, and scientific laboratories.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To accomplish this, Mecka uses a distributed network of human contributors equipped with custom wearable body sensors and standard smartphones. The resulting first-person multimodal data is aggregated into Mecka&#8217;s core dataset, known as Egoverse. This proprietary repository maps how humans move, interact with physical environments, and manipulate everyday objects.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/blackstone-raises-13-1b-in-major-fund-boost/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Blackstone Raises $13.1B in Major Fund Boost</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">An Internal Engine for 3D Tracking</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Once the raw human data streams into Mecka’s systems, it is processed through internal engineering labs. Advanced computer vision models transform ordinary video and sensor inputs into precise 3D spatial reconstructions and highly accurate human motion tracking pathways.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This data acts as a foundational training blueprint for robotics hardware. By studying the Egoverse dataset, frontier model teams and enterprise customers can train neural networks on how a human naturally balances, reaches into a cabinet, handles fragile objects, or navigates a crowded room. This significantly accelerates the path from a laboratory prototype to a commercially viable machine capable of handling autonomous tasks.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The market demand for refined physical data has already achieved remarkable commercial success for the young startup, which was founded in 2025. Under the leadership of CEO Josh Gao, Mecka claims it has already captured an annual recurring revenue run rate of $100 million based on signed enterprise contracts, though the specific names of its early robotics customers remain undisclosed.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Scaling Up Global Operations</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With $60 million in fresh capital, Mecka’s immediate focus is expanding its technical workforce beyond its current roster of 40 employees. The company is actively scaling its data engineering and machine learning research teams to handle the massive influx of real-world data.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Furthermore, the funding will fuel the expansion of Mecka’s global data capture infrastructure. The firm is expanding its multi-country footprint, including scaling up localised field operations, data collection hubs, and annotation management programs across key strategic geographies such as the Philippines.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">By building out this highly specialised data supply chain, Mecka aims to position itself as an indispensable utility for the robotics boom, ensuring that no matter who wins the race to build the best humanoid hardware, everyone will need to use Mecka&#8217;s data layer to give those machines a human-like understanding of reality.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/mecka-ai-raises-60m-to-train-robots-with-human-data/" data-wpel-link="internal">Mecka AI Raises $60M to Train Robots With Human Data</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
