					<description><![CDATA[<p>Momentum in Asia&#8217;s commercial space market has gone into high gear, with South Korean space launch startup Unastella announcing completion of its Series B round of funding, amounting to 33.5</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/unastella-raises-24m-series-b-for-korean-rocket-launches/" data-wpel-link="internal">Unastella Raises $24M Series B for Korean Rocket Launches</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Momentum in Asia&#8217;s commercial space market has gone into high gear, with South Korean space launch startup </span><a href="https://www.unastella.com/en/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Unastella </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">announcing completion of its Series B round of </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/endra-raises-50m-to-automate-data-centre-design/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, amounting to 33.5 billion won ($24 million). The event has put the spotlight back on the international market for small, satellite-specific launch services and local Asia-Pacific ecosystem maturation.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The financial round was headed by Altos Ventures, a well-renowned venture capital investor. The round secured numerous financial investors, including Korea Development Bank, Strong Ventures, KDB Capital, Woori Venture Partners, Samho Green Investment, and Hana Ventures. It marks the total fundraising amount of Unastella at around 61.5 billion won (44 million USD) for the first time.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Breakthrough Architecture for the Global Market</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founded in February 2022, Unastella has become known for its affordable and efficient architecture in an industry plagued by ever-increasing budgets and procrastination. With a miniscule two-dozen-employee herd and in-house development, the plant is based in Seoul, South Korea, and specializes in rapid prototyping.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_202203" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202203" class="size-large wp-image-202203" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/unastella-1024x1024.jpg" alt="unastella" width="1024" height="1024" /><p id="caption-attachment-202203" class="wp-caption-text">Source: unastella</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The genesis of the Unastella design is the implementation of an electric motor-pump cycle engine system. Earth-orbit rocket designs have traditionally operated with high temperatures, complicated gases, generators or staged combustion cycle turbines bolted onto the pumps to provide pressure to the combustors, but Unastella skips this entire ordeal by having custom electric engines and ultralightweight batteries that exclusively power the rocket&#8217;s fuel pumps. This pairs liquid oxygen with conventional rocket-grade kerosene.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">While eliminating the use of superheated turbopumps with battery-powered electric pumps may translate to a reduction in maximum payload throughput, it reduces the production run time and workload by a significant factor, allowing the fledgling startup to put its time and money into ultra-fast commercial service.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/endra-raises-50m-to-automate-data-centre-design/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Endra Raises $50M to Automate Data Centre Design</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Proving Capability on Domestic Soil</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company announced the successful validation of Unastella&#8217;s nimble approach on May 28, 2025. It tested and launched the first of its homegrown prototypes, the UNA EXPRESS I, at a dedicated testing yard in Goheung, South Jeolla Province. The launch event was a turning point in the &#8220;New Space&#8221; era in South Korea, as it was the first time a local private company soloed the design and configuration, built the hardware and launched a liquid-fuel rocket domestically.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Beyond performance testing, the flight was also precedent-setting for South Korea&#8217;s bureaucratic structure. Unastella tested difficult domestic operational logistics and field management procedures and safety licensing protocols, setting the way for future private sector space players in South Korea. The first test vehicle delivered experimental microgravity instrumentation lent by five state research agencies (including the Korea Aerospace Research Institute and the Korea Institute of Machinery).</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Strategic Roadmap: Scaling Up</span></h2>
<p>The Series B funding targets a huge infrastructure build-up and further research and development. The corporation primarily aims to enhance its proprietary propulsion technology, using electric motor pump patents transferred through strategic agreements with KARI.</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Unastella is using the funding to ready its next-generation launch vehicle, UNA EXPRESS II. The main structural objective is to reach the far side of the Kármán line, or 100 kilometres high. This physical marker has proven to be a decisive leading indicator of higher-level commercial deals with global aerospace companies and satellite operators.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Unastella is also in negotiations for a private civilian launch facility at the Naro Space Center that will keep future manifests secure as the company looks to move away from testing suborbital flights and toward commercial microsatellite services and eventually crewed suborbital human spaceflight62.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/unastella-raises-24m-series-b-for-korean-rocket-launches/" data-wpel-link="internal">Unastella Raises $24M Series B for Korean Rocket Launches</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
