					<description><![CDATA[<p>Ilant Health Raises New Capital for Growth Ilant Health has raised $15 million in Series A funding. With this latest investment round, the total funding for Ilant has surpassed $22</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/ilant-health-raises-15-million-obesity-care/" data-wpel-link="internal">Ilant Health Raises $15 Million to Expand Value-Based Obesity Care</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Ilant Health Raises New Capital for Growth</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Ilant Health has raised $15 million in Series A funding. With this latest investment round, the total funding for Ilant has surpassed $22 million. The funding trend toward treatments that manage obesity is growing among health providers hoping to create better health outcomes while managing expenses.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Cornucopian Capital led the Series A financing round, and new investors to Ilant included naturalX, Peakbridge, Semcap AI, Evidenced, and Operator Partners. Returning investors Celtic, LifeX and AlphaLab also invested in the round.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Ilant Health was founded by Elina Onitskansky. The company works with employers and health plans by providing clinicians to lead obesity treatment programs designed for sustained health improvements, instead of merely managing the cost and availability of treatments.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding will allow Ilant to expand its offerings with more employers and health organizations in need of solutions to manage obesity.</span></p>
<h2><b>Clinical Results Demonstrate Strong Outcomes</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Obesity remains one of the most significant healthcare challenges worldwide. Rising rates of obesity continue increasing healthcare costs for employers, insurers, and healthcare systems. Many organisations are searching for models that deliver measurable results.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Ilant reported encouraging early outcomes across its member population. According to company data, participants achieve an average weight loss of 15%. This result exceeds outcomes commonly reported in broader real-world treatment settings.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company also reported improvements beyond weight reduction. Members experienced positive changes in health indicators and overall wellbeing. Patients gained an average of two additional mentally healthy days each month.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">These results stem from a personalised treatment approach. Ilant uses clinical, behavioural, and personal health data to determine appropriate treatment pathways. Care plans are adjusted continuously according to patient progress and response.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Treatment options include behavioural therapy, prescription medications, and </span><a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/computer-science/surgical-intervention" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">surgical interventions</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> when appropriate. The programme also addresses nutrition, physical activity, and stress management. This broader approach aims to support sustainable health improvements rather than short-term results.</span></p>
<h2><b>Personalised Treatment Model Attracts Employers<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_202199" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202199" class="size-full wp-image-202199" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/create-a-futuristic-neon-lit-poster-elem_7lOVNYJuWDu2oxR7-FY5MA_sB8L07ZtSjeWsgpd6rOSOg_cover.png" alt="Personalised obesity care model with health data tracking and employer cost analytics." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-202199" class="wp-caption-text">Ilant’s value-based approach aligns clinical outcomes with cost-efficient obesity care. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Many employers face increasing pressure to provide obesity treatment benefits. At the same time, they must manage rising healthcare spending. New classes of weight-loss medications have increased both opportunity and financial complexity.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Ilant positions itself as a value-based care provider. The company seeks to improve outcomes while controlling total treatment costs. This approach has attracted interest from employers looking for measurable returns on healthcare investments.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Kenneth Gardner of SEIU 775 Benefits Group highlighted the company’s analytical approach. He noted that Ilant evaluates member populations carefully before recommending treatment strategies. This process helps identify individuals most likely to benefit clinically and financially.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Patient experience also plays an important role in the company’s model. Employers working with Ilant have reported positive member feedback. Patients frequently cite personalised support and ongoing engagement throughout treatment.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company has already established relationships with several healthcare partners. These collaborations demonstrate growing demand for integrated obesity care solutions. Employers increasingly prefer comprehensive models over fragmented treatment programmes.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: <a href="https://ventureburn.com/tavo-biotherapeutics-secures-17-million-ophthalmology-development/" data-wpel-link="internal">Tavo Biotherapeutics Secures $17 Million to Advance Glaucoma and Retinal Disease Therapies</a></span></p>
<h2><b>Direct Drug Contracting Supports Cost Control</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Prescription obesity medications are already an issue in most healthcare markets. Increasing demand for GLP-1s has complicated things for employers as they try to reconcile expanding access with remaining budget concerns. Most companies find it a challenge to offer access and still manage pharmacy spend that has become quite significant. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As such, Ilant began to offer direct contracting and transparent pricing in 2025. This allows Ilant to collaborate with pharma companies such as Lilly and Novo Nordisk to improve medication access and give transparency around medication pricing. This allows employers to have better insight and ability to predict their spend and make coverage decisions based on real data. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Employers have two problematic options when it comes to prescription obesity medication: Expanding coverage and higher pharmacy spend, or limiting access and higher potential negative health outcomes. Ilant sees neither option as viable in the long term. Instead, its model seeks to improve the way care is delivered while controlling disease burden and costs. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Cornucopian Capital views obesity and cardiometabolic disease as major healthcare opportunities. The firm believes these areas present significant long-term growth potential. According to Cornucopian, future healthcare leaders will be defined by outcomes. The firm believes technology alone will not determine market leadership.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Ilant plans to use the funding to accelerate its expansion. The company is growing during a period of strong market demand. Its model combines personalised therapy and clinical supervision. It also includes behavioural support and transparent pricing structures.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Ilant aims to build a more sustainable approach to obesity care. The company believes value-based healthcare will become increasingly important. It sees these models as effective tools for managing chronic disease. They may also help employers and payers control healthcare spending.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
